Reasons # 2,830,271,620,302 for becoming an #EDUCATOR full-time and a fashion designer part-time. The industry is pretty cut throat and we need to prepare our students for that world. 

If there is any positive impact I want to have on my students’ career paths it’s that they feel encouraged and motivated to pursue their future in fashion. 

Fashion education should be informative based on experience and excelling the skills of those we have the awesome privilege of sharing them with. 

It’s incredible young minds like this student who we build up and prepare for the fashion field through encouragement and positive reinforcement. Thanks for being a constant inspiration Tommyana! It’s moments like these that remind me I love teaching!!!

xo,

Fairy Gawd Muva

#fashioneducation #professor #gratitude

#RIP #VivienneWestwood and to thank you for easily one of the most pivotal moments of my design career - interning and experiencing an incredible summer at @viviennewestwood studio in Battersea, London. Thank you for being a timeless, kind, and absolutely punk rock icon. 

I remember one afternoon the design studio manager asked if any interns were familiar with Photoshop/Illustrator… thankfully, at the time it was very common to learn Adobe suites in the states in university level. That was the open door to experiencing hands on with the design team. One of the assistant designers walked me ALL the way up to the top of her building to visit her personal design space and somehow by the grace of Vivienne herself - we had a full blown conversation regarding a gown toile that was currently being finalized for a model fitting. Talk about fate, right place right time moment. 

When I say, changed my life, nothing inspired me more than the opportunity to work there and have creative conversation with her. 

Rest in peace Vivienne, and to the interns, Design team, memories I have, and to this #sexandthecity #careybradshaw moment 😭 thank you.

So long 2022!!! #ayearinreview #happynewyear #smellyalater here’s to bigger and more fantastic accomplishments in 2023!

Proud of my students, all of their hard work and dedication motivates me every day to expand and evolve my own goals.  Here’s to becoming a full-time fashion design professor, designing many more collections for fashion week, writing a book, learning piano, a second language, and all the unknown the new year has to offer. 

*pictured here at my first ever college professor gig! 🎉🎉🎉

Start with momentum, in full swing. #newyearsresolution focus on my goals, both short term and long! 

Consistency and perseverance aren’t as easy as they sound, but one of my aspirations for 2023 is to keep my self busy with my own projects and prioritize my time spent on them. 

#fashiondesign #fashionillustration #illustration #copic #prismacolor #chartpak #markerrendering

One of the biggest perks of being a fashion design educator would definitely be the bragging rights of my students’ works. 

The most rewarding reason to take a social media hiatus is to focus on real world trajectory - in this case, college portfolio building. 

After many years of experience in the fashion industry, one thing I never stopped being active with is fine arts. I think the current state of fashion is so infatuated with fast fashion, nepo babies, algorithms… that we lose sight of what fashion is really about. Aside from the obvious expression through aesthetic representation blah blah blah… watching a gown be built by hand, a sketchbook, or a painting grow from zero to 💯 is absolutely priceless. I love my career. 

The first image is a gown that was entirely hand draped and tacked from a sail boat #spinnaker… unbelievably beautiful piece. Sketchbook pages documenting the creative process. And lastly, a completely experiential piece - ALL done by the SAME student. 

Try new things people! The industry needs diversity in your expression of what represents YOU as a designer and an artist. 

#fashiondesign #collegeportfolio #fashionportfolio #draping #illustration #mixedmedium #spraypaint

Helen+Portfolio’s 4ever ♥️
We’ve been grinding the last two months building some monumental student work to show off to the biggest and best #fashioncolleges in the world. 

It’s so rewarding seeing my students take the skills I provide them, and evolve their work before my eyes! (And yours) thanks for watching and supporting y’all!!! And send the best out to my high school seniors in my fashion enrichment/college prep program on their career endeavors. 

#goat #fashiondesign #fashionportfolio #collegeportfolio #fashioninstituteoftechnology #parsons #centralsaintmartins

Fashion design, video editing, content creator… never a dull moment. But I should probably clean my screen before sharing dumb hilarious daily moments in my content creating/education based life. 

Ya win some ya lose some, and sometimes you even lose your mind a little and that’s a totally ok thing! 

#liveyourlife #content #videoediting #imovie #ayecaramba #fashion #youtube #hemmingpants #beethoven

When the time is right, you cross paths with your ride or die! I’m one lucky duck. 

Through all the ups and downs and challenges in my teaching career, no one has been as supportive and motivating as @tomkatpedals we bought a house together in 2019, somehow survived the pandemic without me killing him (based on cabin fever, and me not doing well mentally during lockdown) and here we are 4 years later in our home and I couldn’t be more grateful for where our path has lead. 

Juggling teaching at a university, a high school, on #patreon AND maintaining my design business has been no easy feat. Meanwhile I can’t physically juggle. I’m planning and preparing for the next chapter in our lives/careers/adventures and I’m definitely going to prioritize my well-being and cut out a lot of toxic nonsense that has no business being in my life. 

I just wanted to jump on here and share my gratitude to all of you for being part of my journey, and as I try to continue navigating through where life (and particularly hard work, not ‘manifesting’ through hoping things will happen…) I realize I’m in a really good place and can’t wait to share how everything evolves. 

Also, if you’ve made it this far in the caption; consider removing your self from the equation once in a while. Realization of what you’ve earned and gained through dedication and persistence is ok. It’s ok to feel proud. Don’t forget to help others along the way, especially if you are able to. Take deep breathes, consider the impact on others and don’t be afraid to ask for help when you need it. 

I’m looking forward to sharing more about my life and how overcoming some battles, don’t have to be handled alone. Thank you Tombo for being my bestie and always encouraging me to follow through with my aspirations. 

#payitforward #vulnerability #realtalk

Draping, pattern making, sample making, one woman show. 

#nyfw #fashiondesigner #entrepreneur #couture #bespoke #patternmaking
@melindadimauro and I making #NYFW magic happen.

Look 6: Lace-cage corset and bias skirt. 

Using all dead stock and vintage fabrics for this collection. 

A labor of love, this two piece look from my #AW23 collection features some risky moves, a flat-front #corset pattern I’ve been toying with for ages that has evolved to include hip panels and a longer torso, a lace-cage (single continuous piece of lace draped over a foundation, hand tacked) and a freehand seamless bias skirt. 

This was my first dedicated creative (fashion week) Photoshoot session with @melindadimauro since pre-pandemic. It felt so natural and relentlessly awesome to work with one of my oldest and dearest friends again. Here’s to many more projects together. 

And a massive congratulations to her on the opening of @edenstudionyc this space is surreal, and you can rent it for your events/shoots as well as her incredible photography. 

Can’t wait to share more of my newest collection with you all. 

#couture #corset #lace #redcarpet #eveningwear #fashiondesign

Look 3: Silk Gazaar Bustier Drape Dress

I wanted to create some pieces for this seasons collection that embodied a sense of French #baroque mindfulness and attention to detail. Naturally, with a modern flare in the hand sculpted and draped skirt and particularly the playful length. 

Nothing feels more rewarding than creating within no bounds. 

#NYFW #fashionweek #couture #bustier #corset #patternmaking #eveningwear #elegant

Look 2: Deadstock Jersey Draped Corset Gown

This bodice was a play on an earlier corset I’ve debuted in my collections, I wanted to lengthen the torso and add a dramatic hourglass silhouette all in one piece. Playing with knits and women’s in tandem is also very challenging, but it feels good to accomplish goals with designing new pieces. 

Wasn’t the easiest attempt to align the pattern from panel to panel, but I’m happy with the outcome. Little mistakes are some times overshadowed by the overall success of the look. 

#nyfw #newyorkfashionweek #patternmaking #draping #baroque #couture #knits #wovens #bespoke #tailormade

Look 1: Silk Gazaar Bias Gown

Something I recall explicitly from studying at @fitnyc was learning #couture sewing techniques, and using them as a signature in a lot of my evening gowns. 

For this #bustier style bodice I hand draped bias strips in mitered sections to create more movement and compliment the fluidity of the skirt draped on bias as well. 

Have you worked with bias before? What was your biggest challenge with it?

#nyfw #newyorkfashionweek #aw23 #fashion #fashiondesign #onewomanoperation #patternmaking #draping

TW: When your design dreams HAPPEN, don’t be afraid to literally express your emotions to the point that you scare your self and don’t let your ego withhold you from sharing that with the internet. 

Digitizing my patterns is KILLING me in the best kind of way, like I feel so empowered to have my patterns in ALL sizes.

I plan to start selling these corsets cut&sewn in sizes 0-30, nothing but #sustainablefabrics as I’ve always only sourced (sorry trend wave surfers, this isn’t a new concept…) but holy smokes... I feel so fulfilled seeing my brand evolve like this. 

It’s been an uphill battle, even with having been a finalist SO close to the end in each of my #projectrunway seasons. That show definitely was a great opportunity, but if you’re not working hard afterward/sacrificing, making your own money and moves - that’s why most of us don’t blow up to the degree we’d hope to after filming. No selling out, no nepo baby moments, and no meaningless partnerships here. 

Alright, enough emotional word vomit for one post! Thanks for supporting me and following along on my design journey. 

#fashiondesigner #couture #patternmaker #patterndrafting #digitalpatterns

Can’t say I have much experience with shoe making, but if you need zippers, trims, and notions I got you covered. #SILthread is my go-to in the #garmentdistrictnyc and thankfully we found all we needed to successfully make a pair of #mohair #thighhighboots

Shinjuku, my new favorite city. 🇯🇵

If you haven’t traveled to #Japan you need to get yourself tickets asap. I met so many incredibly nice and joyful, kind/polite/considerate people on this trip to Shinjuku and the surrounding prefectures of Tokyo. 

It’s impossible not to be smitten when the culture, especially the food and atmosphere… coming from someone sensitive to eggs, dairy, and water pH… I felt like a million bucks in Japan and the currency exchange didn’t hurt. 

Next stop, real estate office! Where do you suggest I look in the Shinjuku area for an apartment? I will be back this summer! Can’t wait for more adventures.

When the student becomes the teacher. 

It’s hard but inevitable that the end of the semester comes each year, but to see my students put all of their hard work and talents together, and evolve and grow as a team, readying themselves to tackle the real world and fashion industry - is what makes it worth collaborating with them on their design education path. 

It’s definitely an exhausting and emotionally tolling experience teaching an elective course. But the dozen or so students in the batch who pursue this path as a serious long term commitment are what motivate me to find better and stronger opportunities for what I have to offer those career driven individuals. 

The best part of watching their journey continue to grow, is that I was able to encourage and teach them to build the foundation for it to sprout from. 

#fashionprofessor #fashionphotograhy #fashionshoot

One academic school year’s worth of designs, flawlessly executed and presented by my soon to be #FIT #fashiondesign major - @zaarzuelaa 

You put together one helluva show and I can’t thank you and your models enough for their dedication and time to this project. 

Here’s to the future of fashion. And many thanks and congratulations to all the students who showed in tonight’s runway presentation. You are ALL an inspiration!

#studentwork #runwayshow #talent #driven #dedication #collection #fashionshow

Art director, photographer, set design, styling… 

When you’re working with a team of people who are dedicated, driven, passionate, and trust your process - the outcome is literal high fashion.

@zaarzuelaa is #FIT (Fashion Institute of Technology) bound this September to study womenswear design and after 4 years of mentoring, sent him off with this Photoshoot to capture his portfolio designs. 

It’s no small feat to build a set, styling hair, collaborate on location scouting, help build a brand, and watch it all unfold to be captured in some outstanding photos. It’s the end of an era to send off your star student to the real world and off to college, but it is rewarding to see his world evolve and be proud of. 

Thanks for being persistent through a pandemic, coming back to school full force with your passion for this career, and creating fantastic work that will rock the fashion industry. Now finish that website already! 🤩🤩🤩 @zaarzuelaa

Beautiful bride, best friend, and client! 

Thank you @ciaoallie for designing this dream gown with me for your gorgeous wedding day. 

We worked together on this design for months, taking inspiration from a few pieces she had tried on - but no dress was perfect. Nothing is more special then collaborating with a client (and best friend or 14+ years!!!) on something so monumentally special. 

I absolutely love you and your kindness for having me be part of this moment in your life. Between buying the fabric together (it’s true, the first one is always THE one), working on the physics of that removable cape/sleeve moment, and most of all - the first time you introduced me to your forever person! 

All of those details are forever embodied in your wedding dress. Love is the best thing ever, and I being part of its journey for you and your husband (!!!) leaves me feeling so incredible alive. Ok, enough of my soft side! 

#weddingday #bridal #weddingdress #bride #comission #custom #couture #applique #lace

Inspiration to reality in 8 seconds?

Or more like Instagram versus reality… it’s all fun and games in a quick ass reel! But this has been fit adjustments on top of sewing corrections, seam ripping, realigning notches, plus some sweat and tears... 

Planning a #NYFW event solo is also a jane of many trades type scenario, wearing many hats and filling many different (ill-fitting) shoes. But when you truly have passion to pursue your design career, there’s something inside of you that pushes you to keep up the hard work and momentum despite feeling really run down from being a one woman operation. 

The whole #deadstock movement is something designers such as my self have been sourcing from since the beginning of our careers. It’s important to be on a budget too, and that works for my pocket/ROI when I’m a little more aware of what and why I use the materials I choose. It’s actually cheaper to buy remnant fabrics and way more special to a brand when most of my pieces are one-off. 

Thanks for following along on my design journey! Ill share more of my design process for my upcoming event as I continue making progress. 

#fashion #fashiondesign #consciousfashion #ecofashion #couture #bustier

Walking 20k steps a day… but hey, when you’re with good company it’s worth it. BRB while we eat more bread, almost step in more street 💩 and absorb tons of controversial (yet profoundly inspiring) history. 

#Paris #baguette #louvre #metro #vacation

#NYFW incoming. 

Big changes, rebirth, lots of exciting commitments on the horizon. 

Especially feeling like I can settle in to enjoying being creative again by eliminating toxic obstacles in my path. Looking forward to sharing this collection with all of you, it’s been a bumpy summer but I’m definitely feeling a sense of peace of mind and joy again with my design work. Essential income/life balance can have such a heavy toll on your creative endeavors. But don’t give up! Find the right path for you and your mental health, and don’t forget to always CREATE. 

#fabricshopping #fashionillustration #moodboard #balance #fashiondesign #couture

I’m not sure how I ended up in the place I am now (I mean aside from hard work, lots of blood, sweat, and  plenty of ‘after school special’ tears) but I feel so overwhelmingly grateful and fortunate to be able to express my designs with no restrictions and work with fantastic people who help bring them to life. 

I couldn’t do all that I have accomplished in my life and career without the support and kindness of creatives who share the same passion for design and expression as the team I worked with during this season of #NYFW 

I can’t wait to share more of what I’ve created for this collection. I feel like with each design, pattern development, fabric sourcing, I just feel more and more in tune with my true aesthetic. 

Shout out to my girl squad for making magic happen! I can’t wait to create together again soon.

#SS24 #NYFW Look 1

On the gorgeous @kimbraaudrey in from Paris! 

How wild is that?! Reconnecting with this goddess was on a whole other level, when a model/muse give even more life to your designs it changes the entire trajectory of a project. 

My inspiration for this collection was to take a bit of Degas’ dancers, surrealism, the gardens at Versailles, and a bit of turn of the century structural elements. 

I feel really proud. Thanks for letting me share my world with all of you. There’s something super rewarding about being able to create and show you the process and the entire vision come together.

I timed how long this collection took to design, cut, and sew:

I wish I was exaggerating when I say a collective 516 hours! Absolutely manic, between sketching, draping, selecting fabrics over the span of 6 weeks. Beautiful Camila! #ABT muse for the fall ‘23 gala

@abtofficial opening night this past week. Thank you so much Camila for trusting me and I look forward to many more red carpets together. 

It’s fun working with a client even if it’s a virtual experience. Camila sent me one inspiration word: rock. And I thought to my self, how do we make this glitter glam edgy yet sophisticated. The answer is sequins and a sharp neckline, little fancy beaded Chantilly lace to soften the moment - voila, how to make a ballerina even more graceful. 

#metgala #eveningwear #gown #sequin #redcarpet #ballet #ballerina

Got hitched! Was no small feat, considering we planned a super small, extremely private ceremony with just our parents and siblings - still felt like a tan a marathon! And I am not the runner in this couple. 🫠

I wanted everything to embody romance and obviously compassion/love all that mushy stuff, so we decided on a theme together, painted and created all of the invites and favors, picked fabrics together (a week ahead, because who would I be if I spent more than a few days on any project, there’s the Project Runway PTSD…)

We even made the center piece, after many a Pinterest board… but I like sharing my life and accomplishments on here! Sometimes, there’s things we don’t have to feel obligated to share - but this is one of the biggest decisions I’ve ever made. And best. Thanks for being my dude @tomkatpedals excited for the future and craziness ahead. 

#bridal #lace #chantillylace #lace #custom #wedding #coutureinspired

That’s a wrap! @fitnyc feels like my home away from home. (And where I’ve been hiding from Instagram this semester)

If you asked me a year ago, if I would be teaching at my alma mater - I’d have probably responded with something overwhelmingly negative about my self. I took the plunge last month and left one of my teaching jobs that was outrageously toxic and unfulfilling, to focus my time, energy, and professional life in a way more rewarding position at FIT. My contributions aren’t taken for granted here, I’m embraced as part of the team, my mentors are extremely selfless and talented, always willing to teach and guide me to being the best educator and version of my self. 

Something about mental health and well-being that finally dawned on me as being a priority (duh), and look at me now! Took a major risk by leaving one job and closing the door on the chapter of my teaching career, and jumping forward in to higher Ed! No turning back. 

Professor Castillo at your service. 

#FIT #fashiondesign #mentalwellness #selfcare #professor #livingmybestlife

Time flies when you’re #reachingoals 

2023 was probably, easily the most bumpy road but it ended with a bang. Making this reel puts things in to perspective, especially for the new year. 

-NYFW
-Made my best friend’s wedding dress 
-Dream vacation with my dreamboat to Japan
-Began my second year as a Fashion professor 
-Stressed all summer looking for a way out of a toxic job
-Found a non-toxic job with room to grow and support from my team!!! (FIT)
-Went to Paris/Versailles and got engaged!!!
-Got married spontaneously and made my dress in 2-3 weeks because I couldn’t wait to be a Mrs!
-NYFW collection I actually felt really confident with
-Headed in to the new year on a family vacation 😵‍💫

I am very grateful, and especially with having the ability to honestly say I’m taking less for granted. Focusing on my goals and MY health and well-being for 2024. 

Cutting out toxic nonsense seriously clears your mind and path for nothing but positive energy and a better appreciation for the actual important things in your life. 

#♥ #hopefulfor #health #bliss #nyfw2023 #fashionprofessor #fashiondesign #higheredlife #cruisehopeidontfalloverboard
